 964        /// <summary>
 965        /// Returns the target of the specified browse path fragment(s).
 966        /// </summary>
 967        /// <remarks>
 968        /// If reference exists but the node manager does not know the browse name it must
 969        /// return the NodeId as an unresolvedTargetIds. The caller will try to check the
 970        /// browse name.
 971        /// </remarks>
 972        public virtual void TranslateBrowsePath(
 973            OperationContext context,
 974            object sourceHandle,
 975            RelativePathElement relativePath,
 976            IList<ExpandedNodeId> targetIds,
 977            IList<NodeId> unresolvedTargetIds) {
 0978            var systemContext = SystemContext.Copy(context);
 0979            IDictionary<NodeId, NodeState> operationCache = new NodeIdDictionary<NodeState>();
 980
 0981            lock (Lock) {
 982                // verify that the node exists.
 0983                var source = IsHandleInNamespace(sourceHandle);
 984
 0985                if (source == null) {
 0986                    return;
 987                }
 988
 989                // validate node.
 0990                if (!ValidateNode(systemContext, source)) {
 0991                    return;
 992                }
 993
 994                // get list of references that relative path.
 0995                var browser = source.CreateBrowser(
 0996                    systemContext,
 0997                    null,
 0998                    relativePath.ReferenceTypeId,
 0999                    relativePath.IncludeSubtypes,
 01000                    relativePath.IsInverse ? BrowseDirection.Inverse : BrowseDirection.Forward,
 01001                    relativePath.TargetName,
 01002                    null,
 01003                    false);
 1004
 1005                // check the browse names.
 1006                try {
 01007                    for (var reference = browser.Next(); reference != null; reference = browser.Next()) {
 1008                        // ignore unknown external references.
 01009                        if (reference.TargetId.IsAbsolute) {
 1010                            continue;
 1011                        }
 1012
 01013                        NodeState target = null;
 1014
 1015                        // check for local reference.
 1016
 01017                        if (reference is NodeStateReference referenceInfo) {
 01018                            target = referenceInfo.Target;
 1019                        }
 1020
 01021                        if (target == null) {
 01022                            var targetId = (NodeId)reference.TargetId;
 1023
 1024                            // the target may be a reference to a node in another node manager.
 01025                            if (!IsNodeIdInNamespace(targetId)) {
 01026                                unresolvedTargetIds.Add((NodeId)reference.TargetId);
 01027                                continue;
 1028                            }
 1029
 1030                            // look up the target manually.
 01031                            target = GetManagerHandle(systemContext, targetId, operationCache) as NodeState;
 1032
 01033                            if (target == null) {
 1034                                continue;
 1035                            }
 1036                        }
 1037
 1038                        // check browse name.
 01039                        if (target.BrowseName == relativePath.TargetName) {
 01040                            targetIds.Add(reference.TargetId);
 1041                        }
 1042                    }
 01043                }
 1044                finally {
 01045                    browser.Dispose();
 01046                }
 1047            }
 01048        }

 1050        /// <summary>

 01481                        var operation = new ReadWriteOperationState {
 01482                            Source = source,
 01483                            Index = ii
 01484                        };
 1485
 01486                        nodesToValidate.Add(operation);
 1487
 01488                        continue;
 1489                    }
 1490
 1491                    // historical data not available.
 01492                    errors[ii] = StatusCodes.BadHistoryOperationUnsupported;
 1493                }
 1494
 1495                // check for nothing to do.
 01496                if (nodesToValidate.Count == 0) {
 01497                    return;
 1498                }
 1499
 1500                // validates the nodes (reads values from the underlying data source if required).
 01501                for (var ii = 0; ii < nodesToValidate.Count; ii++) {
 01502                    var operation = nodesToValidate[ii];
 1503
 01504                    if (!ValidateNode(systemContext, operation.Source)) {
 1505                        continue;
 1506                    }
 1507
 1508                    // historical data not available.
 01509                    errors[ii] = StatusCodes.BadHistoryOperationUnsupported;
 1510                }
 01511            }
 01512        }

 1514        /// <summary>
 1515        /// Calls a method on the specified nodes.
 1516        /// </summary>
 1517        public virtual void Call(
 1518            OperationContext context,
 1519            IList<CallMethodRequest> methodsToCall,
 1520            IList<CallMethodResult> results,
 1521            IList<ServiceResult> errors) {
 01522            var systemContext = SystemContext.Copy(context);
 01523            IDictionary<NodeId, NodeState> operationCache = new NodeIdDictionary<NodeState>();
 01524            var nodesToValidate = new List<CallOperationState>();
 1525
 01526            lock (Lock) {
 01527                for (var ii = 0; ii < methodsToCall.Count; ii++) {
 01528                    var methodToCall = methodsToCall[ii];
 1529
 1530                    // skip items that have already been processed.
 01531                    if (methodToCall.Processed) {
 1532                        continue;
 1533                    }
 1534
 1535                    // check for valid handle.
 1536
 01537                    if (!(GetManagerHandle(systemContext, methodToCall.ObjectId, operationCache) is NodeState source)) {
 1538                        continue;
 1539                    }
 1540
 1541                    // owned by this node manager.
 01542                    methodToCall.Processed = true;
 1543
 1544                    // find the method.
 01545                    var method = source.FindMethod(systemContext, methodToCall.MethodId);
 1546
 01547                    if (method == null) {
 1548                        // check for loose coupling.
 01549                        if (source.ReferenceExists(ReferenceTypeIds.HasComponent, false, methodToCall.MethodId)) {
 01550                            method = (MethodState)FindPredefinedNode(methodToCall.MethodId, typeof(MethodState));
 1551                        }
 1552
 01553                        if (method == null) {
 01554                            errors[ii] = StatusCodes.BadMethodInvalid;
 01555                            continue;
 1556                        }
 1557                    }
 1558
 01559                    var result = results[ii] = new CallMethodResult();
 1560
 1561                    // check if the node is ready for reading.
 01562                    if (source.ValidationRequired) {
 01563                        errors[ii] = StatusCodes.BadNodeIdUnknown;
 1564
 1565                        // must validate node in a seperate operation.
 01566                        var operation = new CallOperationState {
 01567                            Source = source,
 01568                            Method = method,
 01569                            Index = ii
 01570                        };
 1571
 01572                        nodesToValidate.Add(operation);
 1573
 01574                        continue;
 1575                    }
 1576
 1577                    // call the method.
 01578                    errors[ii] = Call(
 01579                        systemContext,
 01580                        methodToCall,
 01581                        source,
 01582                        method,
 01583                        result);
 1584                }
 1585
 1586                // check for nothing to do.
 01587                if (nodesToValidate.Count == 0) {
 01588                    return;
 1589                }
 1590
 1591                // validates the nodes (reads values from the underlying data source if required).
 01592                for (var ii = 0; ii < nodesToValidate.Count; ii++) {
 01593                    var operation = nodesToValidate[ii];
 1594
 1595                    // validate the object.
 01596                    if (!ValidateNode(systemContext, operation.Source)) {
 1597                        continue;
 1598                    }
 1599
 1600                    // call the method.
 01601                    var result = results[operation.Index];
 1602
 01603                    errors[operation.Index] = Call(
 01604                        systemContext,
 01605                        methodsToCall[operation.Index],
 01606                        operation.Source,
 01607                        operation.Method,
 01608                        result);
 1609                }
 01610            }
 01611        }

 1613        /// <summary>
 1614        /// Stores the state of a call method operation.
 1615        /// </summary>
 1616        private struct CallOperationState {
 1617            public NodeState Source;
 1618            public MethodState Method;
 1619            public int Index;
 1620        }

 1622        /// <summary>
 1623        /// Calls a method on an object.
 1624        /// </summary>
 1625        protected virtual ServiceResult Call(
 1626            ISystemContext context,
 1627            CallMethodRequest methodToCall,
 1628            NodeState source,
 1629            MethodState method,
 1630            CallMethodResult result) {
 01631            var systemContext = context as ServerSystemContext;
 01632            var argumentErrors = new List<ServiceResult>();
 01633            var outputArguments = new VariantCollection();
 1634
 01635            var error = method.Call(
 01636                context,
 01637                source.NodeId,
 01638                methodToCall.InputArguments,
 01639                argumentErrors,
 01640                outputArguments);
 1641
 01642            if (ServiceResult.IsBad(error)) {
 01643                return error;
 1644            }
 1645
 1646            // check for argument errors.
 01647            var argumentsValid = true;
 1648
 01649            for (var jj = 0; jj < argumentErrors.Count; jj++) {
 01650                var argumentError = argumentErrors[jj];
 1651
 01652                if (argumentError != null) {
 01653                    result.InputArgumentResults.Add(argumentError.StatusCode);
 1654
 01655                    if (ServiceResult.IsBad(argumentError)) {
 01656                        argumentsValid = false;
 1657                    }
 01658                }
 1659                else {
 01660                    result.InputArgumentResults.Add(StatusCodes.Good);
 1661                }
 1662
 1663                // only fill in diagnostic info if it is requested.
 01664                if ((systemContext.OperationContext.DiagnosticsMask & DiagnosticsMasks.OperationAll) != 0) {
 01665                    if (ServiceResult.IsBad(argumentError)) {
 01666                        argumentsValid = false;
 01667                        result.InputArgumentDiagnosticInfos.Add(new DiagnosticInfo(argumentError,
 01668                            systemContext.OperationContext.DiagnosticsMask, false,
 01669                            systemContext.OperationContext.StringTable));
 01670                    }
 1671                    else {
 01672                        result.InputArgumentDiagnosticInfos.Add(null);
 1673                    }
 1674                }
 1675            }
 1676
 1677            // check for validation errors.
 01678            if (!argumentsValid) {
 01679                result.StatusCode = StatusCodes.BadInvalidArgument;
 01680                return result.StatusCode;
 1681            }
 1682
 1683            // do not return diagnostics if there are no errors.
 01684            result.InputArgumentDiagnosticInfos.Clear();
 1685
 1686            // return output arguments.
 01687            result.OutputArguments = outputArguments;
 1688
 01689            return ServiceResult.Good;
 1690        }

 1692        /// <summary>
 1693        /// Subscribes or unsubscribes to events produced by the specified source.
 1694        /// </summary>
 1695        /// <remarks>
 1696        /// This method is called when a event subscription is created or deletes. The node manager
 1697        /// must  start/stop reporting events for the specified object and all objects below it in
 1698        /// the notifier hierarchy.
 1699        /// </remarks>
 1700        public virtual ServiceResult SubscribeToEvents(
 1701            OperationContext context,
 1702            object sourceId,
 1703            uint subscriptionId,
 1704            IEventMonitoredItem monitoredItem,
 1705            bool unsubscribe) {
 01706            var systemContext = SystemContext.Copy(context);
 01707            IDictionary<NodeId, NodeState> operationCache = new NodeIdDictionary<NodeState>();
 1708
 01709            lock (Lock) {
 1710                // check for valid handle.
 01711                var source = IsHandleInNamespace(sourceId);
 1712
 01713                if (source == null) {
 01714                    return StatusCodes.BadNodeIdInvalid;
 1715                }
 1716
 1717                // check if the object supports subscritions.
 1718
 01719                if (!(sourceId is BaseObjectState instance) || instance.EventNotifier != EventNotifiers.SubscribeToEvent
 01720                    return StatusCodes.BadNotSupported;
 1721                }
 1722
 01723                var monitoredNode = instance.Handle as MonitoredNode;
 1724
 1725                // handle unsubscribe.
 01726                if (unsubscribe) {
 01727                    if (monitoredNode != null) {
 01728                        monitoredNode.UnsubscribeToEvents(systemContext, monitoredItem);
 1729
 1730                        // do any post processing.
 01731                        OnUnsubscribeToEvents(systemContext, monitoredNode, monitoredItem);
 1732                    }
 1733
 01734                    return ServiceResult.Good;
 1735                }
 1736
 1737                // subscribe to events.
 01738                if (monitoredNode == null) {
 01739                    instance.Handle = monitoredNode = new MonitoredNode(Server, this, source);
 1740                }
 1741
 01742                monitoredNode.SubscribeToEvents(systemContext, monitoredItem);
 1743
 1744                // do any post processing.
 01745                OnSubscribeToEvents(systemContext, monitoredNode, monitoredItem);
 1746
 01747                return ServiceResult.Good;
 1748            }
 01749        }

 02202                samplingInterval = variable.MinimumSamplingInterval;
